  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The Hotel Punta Maquignaz is owned by the Maquignaz family in Cervinia. Aime Maquignaz is an artist, so expect artistic interiors and individually decorated rooms. The hotel is r</span>ight in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda}" title="Cervinia">Cervinia</a>, just 100 metres from the <span>Campetto Cretaz lift</span>.</p>
<h2>Boutique Hotel</h2>
<p>There's a really cosy feel in the hotel with Alpine features and wood-panelled rooms. The open fire in the lounge is lovely to come back to after a long day of skiing. It's a nice spot to catch up on the day's events with a drink from the bar.</p>
<p><span>You'll find eclectic art everywhere you look and each room has unique pieces of furniture. What we love about this hotel is its cosy alpine atmosphere and its traditional Italian meets 'quirky-boutique' style.</span></p>
<h2>Spa Area</h2>
<p>There's also a spa area, which is included in the hotel price. We love using the sauna to ease those aching muscles. You can even treat yourself to a massage- they can be booked and paid for locally.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Punta Maquignaz the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
